Had PCOS for 13 years but for the past 5 years I’ve nailed it the art of getting my periods on time 🤩
.
🛢️ Castor oil on navel + castor oil pack:
This practice supports lymphatic drainage, liver detox, and pelvic circulation, which can gently support hormonal balance and ease menstrual irregularities.
It’s especially loved in Ayurveda and integrative wellness for endometriosis, PCOS, and cramps
Just avoid during your period or if trying to conceive or is pregnant!

👣 Ghee with Kansa wand on feet:
This is rooted in Ayurveda marma therapy
Massaging ghee (especially at night) with a Kansa wand grounds the body, promotes deep sleep, and reduces Vata imbalance which often drives hormonal chaos 🌪️
Super calming for the nervous system + hormones 🥳

🧘‍♀️ Legs Up the Wall for 30 Minutes
Reduces Cortisol (Stress Hormone)
This pose activates your parasympathetic nervous system — aka the rest and digest mode ☺️
Helps lower stress levels, which directly impacts hormone balance (especially for PCOS, irregular periods, thyroid issues
✨ Less cortisol = better balance of estrogen, progesterone and insulin
.
🚨 Disclaimer : 
I’m not a doctor or health professional — I’m just sharing what’s worked for me through personal experience. Hormonal health is deeply individual, so please consult a gynecologist or certified expert before trying anything new. Always listen to your body first 🥰
.
.

“I lost 5 KGS in 40 days… and no, it wasn’t magic 😜 It was me, ChatGPT and a whole lotta ‘I don’t feel like it but I’ll still do it for myself and for my body 🌸🧿

Here’s the ChatGPT prompt I used to start my weight loss journey! Copy-paste it into ChatGPT and tweak it for your goals👇
Hi ChatGPT, I’m [Your Name], [Your age], [Heigh] and [Weight] , I have PCOS (controlled) if you have otherwise skip this step. I want to lose fat and build lean muscle. I work out 5 days a week. Please give me a weekly workout and diet plan. I eat chicken, eggs, basil seeds, salads, and whey. I avoid dairy and gluten [Based on your eating preference]

I have PCOS!! That means bloating, cravings, low energy, and stubborn fat that just doesn’t wanna leave 🥲!! But this time ChatGPT had a plan!! A real one 😇😝

ChatGPT created my custom 40-day workout + meal plan. No extreme cardio, no starving. Just consistency, patience, and showing up—even when I zero motivation I kept going on 😎

There were days I didn’t wanna move. Days my hormones were raging and my motivation was MIA 🙄But every single time I wanted to quit I reminded myself 👉🏽You’ve done harder things than this Nini ❤️

And guess what? Not only did I lose 5 kilos but I gained something much much bigger ———- discipline, strength, and trust in myself to do anything u out my mind into. I have always been a quitter —— whether it’s quitting alcohol, sugar, bad habits or just bad surroundings I have just failed sooo many times but for the first time this feels like a win. This just keeps me going 🥳

If I can do it with PCOS then 🫵 YOU can do it too!! No shortcuts. Just a smart plan, small steps, and showing up every damn day 🧡
Now just ask ChatGPT and start but also do your research before starting out. In the end it’s your body and you should know about it :)
